            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ECan%20we%20be%20sure%20of%20something%20we%20cannot%20see%3F%20The%20certainty%20of%20faith%20goes%20beyond%20hope.%20Hope%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20future%2C%20our%20eternal%20reward%20once%20this%20life%20is%20over.%20In%20contrast%2C%20faith%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20present.%20The%20King%20James%20Version%20of%20Hebrews%2011%3A1%20begins%20with%20the%20phrase%20%22Now%20faith.%22%20If%20it's%20not%20now%2C%20it's%20not%20faith!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20entire%20concept%20of%20faith%20rests%20on%20being%20certain%20of%20the%20unseen%2C%20because%20all%20creation%20came%20into%20existence%20from%20things%20that%20are%20not%20seen%20(Hebrews%2011%3A3).%20The%20fact%20that%20something%20is%20unseen%20does%20not%20make%20it%20unreal.%20God's%20Word%20operates%20in%20the%20unseen%20realm%2C%20and%20faith%20in%20His%20Word%20is%20what%20brings%20those%20things%20into%20the%20seen%20realm.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIt%20takes%20evidence%2C%20a%20piece%20of%20objective%20data%20in%20which%20you%20place%20your%20full%20confidence%2C%20to%20be%20certain%20of%20something%20you%20cannot%20see.%20The%20promises%20of%20the%20Bible%20must%20become%20your%20evidence%20and%20certainty%20even%20when%20your%20five%20senses%20see%20no%20tangible%20reality%20in%20the%20natural%20world.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFix%20your%20attention%20on%20God's%20promises%20until%20your%20hope%20graduates%20to%20become%20faith!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
